      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POP POP BANG (3) was well supported last time and gave a sight after a fast early split but could manage only the minor money, finishing a half a length second (22.28) over 390m at this track. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Top prospect. KENSINGTON GIRL (8) was a last start winner (22.48) from Box 8 at Warrnambool. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. JUNO USKO (6) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (22.49) at Warrnambool behind Paw Yaris in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win. Has the pace to be prominent. Expecting another good run. MYSTIC CONTESSA (4) is a last-start placegetter who should be thereabouts.",
